E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Xmas Party: It's the end of term and Will has been voted chairman of the Christmas prom committee, so he ropes in Simon, Jay and Neil to help get things organised. (S1 Ep6/6) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Age of Darkness: The family rally round to comfort Erica when she's dumped by her boyfriend Drew. Barry becomes addicted to an arcade video game. (S1 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Wrestler Named Goldberg: Murray coaches Barry for his first high school wrestling match but keeps it a secret from Beverly, who is sure to disapprove. (S1 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: Carl hopes to make a splash in Spain as he aims to marry Rebecca on the Med. But Rebecca has big expectations for a high-class affair. Will Carl's plans make her swoon with delight?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: There's Christmas magic at the McQueens', but for Mercedes, the sparkle has faded... Can Warren help to spread festive cheer? Meanwhile, a knock on the door grants Theresa's wish.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Things are frosty between Misbah and Donny this Christmas, but will the festive cheer bring the family closer together? Or will Donny's recent escapades be exposed?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip featuring animals and food, from the always hilarious Tube that is Rude.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lido Di Manhattan: Ambitious graduate Lisa bought her restaurant in California at just 23 but, five years later, she's worried she picked the wrong venture. Can Gordon help? (S3 Ep8) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Mama Rita's: Gordon tries to bring new ideas to Mama Rita's Mexican restaurant in Newbury Park, southern California. (S3 Ep10) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Livin' on a Prayer: Murray is feted by his old high school for his sporting prowess. Barry throws a party to impress his friends while his parents are away. (S1 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Love Is a Mix Tape: Adam tries to express his feelings for Dana by making her a mix tape, but disaster strikes when the tape falls into Beverly's hands. (S2 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer Is Where the Art Isn't: Homer learns to love a Miro painting. Then it's stolen - and he gets the blame. (S29 Ep12/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: King Leer: Moe inherits a mattress business from his father, then lands in an all-out war with his siblings. (S29 Ep16/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lisa Gets the Blues: Lisa gets the yips and Bart is made to dress up and sing as Annie from the musical. They go to New Orleans to recover. (S29 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 15: The Hawking Excitation: E4's countdown of our top 30 Big Bang episodes continues. Stephen Hawking visits the university. Howard's his chaperone and Sheldon is envious. (S5 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 14: The Countdown Reflection: Bernadette decides that she wants to get married to Howard before his NASA space mission, but can they get organised in time? (S5 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 13: The Long Distance Dissonance: The gang worry when Sheldon's former admirer, Dr Ramona Nowitzki, turns up while Amy is away working at Princeton. (S10 Ep24/24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 12: The Panty Piata Polarization: Sheldon bans Penny from the flat for numerous minor infractions, so she retaliates. Howard and Raj search for the America's Next Top Model house. (S2 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 11: The Lunar Excitation: Raj registers Sheldon for online dating and finds the perfect match: the female version of Sheldon. Penny seduces Leonard while she's drunk. (S3 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 10: The Justice League Recombination: The guys slowly warm to Zack and find an enjoyable way to bond with him when they enter a New Year's Eve fancy dress competition together. (S4 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 9: The Robotic Manipulation: Penny tags along to Sheldon's first date with a woman he's been texting for months. Howard finds a new use for a robotic arm. (S4 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 8: The Barbarian Sublimation: Penny becomes addicted to an online game based on the world of Conan the Barbarian and begins to pester Sheldon for advice. (S2 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 7: The Scavenger Vortex: Raj organises an epic and demanding scavenger hunt, designed to test the friends' scientific knowledge and common sense. (S7 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 6: The Maternal Capacitance: A disastrous visit from Leonard's mother has the unexpected side-effect of bringing Leonard and Penny closer together. (S2 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 5: The Adhesive Duck Deficiency: Leonard, Raj and Howard go on a camping trip that alters their minds. Penny dislocates her shoulder when she slips in the shower. (S3 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 4: The Staircase Implementation: Leonard tells Penny about how he and Sheldon became friends, and the origins of the roommate agreement. (S3 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 3: The Opening Night Excitation: Leonard, Howard and Raj have an extra ticket for the Star Wars movie premiere but can't decide who they should give it to. (S9 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 2: The Bow Tie Asymmetry: Everyone is focused on making sure that the arrangements for Amy and Sheldon's big day go according to plan - except the bride and groom. (S11 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Bang Theory: E4's Favourites
E4Plus1.uk.description: 1: The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis: Here it is - E4's favourite ever Big Bang episode! Don't @ us. Oh OK then, you can. It's the one about Sheldon learning gift-giving etiquette. (S2 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: It's the first Christmas without Peri, but Leela's determined to give her children and Lucas the best day she can, which means making amends with Ste. Meanwhile, Pearl has something to say.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Itchy & Scratchy & Poochie Show: Homer gets a job on The Itchy & Scratchy Show as the voice of hip-hop surfer dog Poochie, a character brought in to boost viewing figures. (S8 Ep14/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: My Sister, My Sitter: Lisa starts a new career as a babysitter. All is going well, until Marge and Homer employ her to look after Bart and Maggie... (S8 Ep17/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer vs the Eighteenth Amendment: When alcohol is banned in Springfield, Moe's Tavern becomes a speakeasy and Homer re-invents himself as the Beer Baron. (S8 Ep18/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: What do Denise Van Outen, Rylan, Gyles Brandreth, Mo Gilligan, Shaun Ryder et al think of Planet Earth II, Big Brother: Best Shows Ever, Grease, Dating Around, Misery and more top telly?

Film4.uk.title: Late Night with the Devil
Film4.uk.description: (2023) Unsettling found-footage horror with David Dastmalchian. A has-been host tries to save his 70s talk show using a demonically possessed 13-year-old girl. Really, what could go wrong?

Film4.uk.title: Carlito's Way
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Brian De Palma's crime thriller with Al Pacino. An ex-con, fresh out of jail, flamboyantly declares his plan to go straight. But his criminal past just won't let him go...

Film4.uk.title: Tooth Fairy
Film4.uk.description: (2010) Family fantasy comedy. Dwayne Johnson stars as a tough ice hockey player who is transformed into a real-life fairy as punishment for telling a child that tooth fairies don't exist.

Film4.uk.title: My Spy
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Family action comedy. A CIA agent (Dave Bautista) gets the run-around from a nine-year-old girl when he's sent to keep an eye on her family. With Chloe Coleman.

Film4.uk.title: One Million Years B.C.
Film4.uk.description: (1966) Raquel Welch - in her famous fur bikini - stars in this prehistoric adventure set in an inhospitable landscape populated by two warring tribes and Ray Harryhausen's roving dinosaurs.

Film4.uk.title: The League of Extraordinary...
Film4.uk.description: ...Gentlemen: (2003) Fantasy with Sean Connery. In an alternative Victorian age, can Allan Quatermain, Dorian Gray, Captain Nemo, Mina Harker and the Invisible Man avert a war?

Film4.uk.title: The Banshees of Inisherin
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Colin Farrell and Brendan Gleeson star in writer and director Martin McDonagh's award-winning tragicomedy about the end of a life-long friendship on a very small island. Awkward.

Film4.uk.title: The Hunt
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Fighty, satirical horror that upset Donald Trump. Hilary Swank plays a rich lefty who likes hunting working class people to the death. But she didn't reckon on Betty Gilpin.

Film4.uk.title: The Worst Person in the World
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Romantic drama. A young woman grapples with her desires. Will her search for the perfect life leave her missing out? In Norwegian/subs. Adults only: strong language/sex/drugs/nudity.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Great Central Railway: Fred visits the Great Central Railway, the only remaining main line railway in the country which still has steam locomotives, where he takes a footplate ride. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Introduction: David Attenborough catalogues life beneath the ocean waves. All manner of spectacular lifeforms dwell deep underwater, from alien monsters to pack-hunting killer whales. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The Deep: The mysteries of the oceans are revealed in this stunning series narrated by David Attenborough. Among the oddities featured here are terrifying fish with massive teeth. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Open Ocean: Oceanic explorations, topped off with David Attenborough's masterful narration. Learn about the predatory skills of some of the planet's most charismatic hunters. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Frozen Seas: David Attenborough salutes the survival techniques of creatures who endure harsh conditions in the Arctic and Antarctic, as the lauded natural history series continues. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Blue Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Seasonal Seas: David Attenborough vividly describes the history of our oceans. Seasonal changes in the richest waters on Earth drive an explosion of life, from seals to jellyfish. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ford Granada/Toyota Hilux: Derek navigates the dry stone walls of the Peak District to collect a very original 1988 Opel Manta. Plus, Dave deals with a Ford Granada rally support vehicle. S6 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bentley T1/Fiesta XR2: Dave's son Jack is heading out to Cheshire to collect two cars with a 35-year age difference. And luckily for Mathewsons, Lucy knows exactly what has been brought in. S3 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Excalibur/Austin 7: A 1970 Excalibur Roadstar, once owned by Roy Orbison, arrives at Thornton le Dale and Derek heads to County Durham to collect a 1935 Austin 7 Ulster that's been rebuilt. S4 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Austin A30/BMW Isetta: Two British classics head into to the Mathewsons' auction room, Dave heads to North Manchester to pick up an Austin A30 and a Morris 8 E with an alternative paint job. S4 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lairg to Caithness: The latest stage of Michael Portillo's trek takes him past lochs and castles on the Far North Line to Britain's northernmost railway station at Thurso. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Thurso to Orkney: Michael Portillo heads for the ferry port of Scrabster to cross the Pentland Firth to the Orkney Islands. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Tynemouth to Bardon Mill: Michael Portillo sets off from Tynemouth on the first leg of a trip to Berwick, hearing about a tragedy that inspired a coastal rescue service. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Newcastle to Lynemouth: Michael Portillo heads from Newcastle to Lynemouth, and is intrigued to hear of its part in Newcastle's early industrial development. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lotus Esprit/MG TF/ERF Lorry: On the way to pick up two lovely '70s Lotus sports cars, Derek takes to the skies for his first ever helicopter flight in a 1967 Bell 47 chopper. S9 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Moskvitch: Dave's drawn to a Fiat Uno 45 in '1970's beige', with 36,000 miles on the clock. S9 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Red Star: Following Operation Barbarossa in 1941, the Soviet Army battled the Germans almost alone for two years. Laurence Olivier recounts their efforts as the epic series continues. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Whirlwind: The ultimate guide to World War II, narrated by Laurence Olivier. Bomber Command are unable to hit their targets precisely and attack German cities under cover of darkness. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Tough Old Gut: The hugely respected chronology of WWII. Churchill described Italy as the 'soft underbelly of the crocodile', thinking the Allies could cut through it to reach Germany. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Jensen Interceptor/Triumph Sprint: Derek auctions off a Jensen Interceptor and a Jensen Healey along with a one-off Wood & Pickett Triumph Dolomite Sprint. S3 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Rover 2000 SC/Triumph Spitfire: A 1971 Mercedes SL and a 1989 Jaguar XJS emerge from a barn on a chicken farm, a Roller and a Rover go under the hammer and a 1966 Triumph Spitfire is restored to near

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Ocean Deep: Witness our planet in its natural glory. David Attenborough looks at life deep undersea, where a 30-tonne whale shark hunts and vampire squid employ bioluminescence. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Islands: Wildlife documentary series presented by David Attenborough, beginning with a look at the remote islands which offer sanctuary to some of the planet's rarest creatures. S2 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Mountains: The wildlife documentary series with David Attenborough continues with a unique and intimate glimpse into the secretive lives of mountain-dwelling animals. S2 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: The End: The first-ever episode of the space comedy! Meet the crew of the Red Dwarf: sole surviving human Lister, hologram Rimmer, and a lifeform evolved from Lister's cat. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Future Echoes: Classic space comedy. Having accelerated for a mere three million years, Red Dwarf breaks through the light barrier and sets off a series of weird occurrences. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Balance of Power: Interstellar laughs from the Red Dwarf crew. Lister is desperate to see dead officer Kochanski once more and begs Rimmer to bring her back as a hologram. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Mediterranean with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Setting off from a snowy mountain ski resort in Cyprus, Simon Reeve finds an island and a capital city still deeply divided between Turkish Cypriots and Greek Cypriots. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Frozen Planet
UAndYesterday.uk.description: To the Ends of the Earth: David Attenborough reveals the vast wilderness of the polar regions. At the North Pole, polar bears court and the sun returns after six months of dark. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Bedford Bus/Triumph TR7: Derek has a three-hour drive in a 1960s bus that arrived in the UK after a life in the sun. Dave takes a Triumph TR7 convertible to auction. S6 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Vanden Plas/Ford Fiesta XR2: Dave's on his way to Grimsby to pick up an iconic 80s fast Ford, the Mk1 Fiesta XR2. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Lotus Esprit/MG TF/ERF Lorry: On the way to pick up two lovely '70s Lotus sports cars, Derek takes to the skies for his first ever helicopter flight in a 1967 Bell 47 chopper. S9 Ep10

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Moskvitch: Dave's drawn to a Fiat Uno 45 in '1970's beige', with 36,000 miles on the clock. S9 Ep11

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Mountains: The wildlife documentary series with David Attenborough continues with a unique and intimate glimpse into the secretive lives of mountain-dwelling animals. S2 Ep2

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Morpeth to Amble: Michael Portillo explores the wild and rugged coastline of Northumberland by rail, beginning in Morpeth. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Alnmouth to Bamburgh: Michael Portillo travels the length of the Northumbrian coastline, and visits the mighty Bamburgh Castle. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Farne Islands to Berwick-upon-Tweed: Michael Portillo's rail trek along the coast of Northumberland continues towards the Farne Islands. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Fairlie to Port Glasgow: Michael Portillo sets off on the first leg of a trip from the Firth of Clyde to Lewis and Harris. S1 Ep16

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Navy Ambo/Plas/Victor/Viscount/Lorry: Paul hits the road to collect an old navy ambulance that served its time as a holiday camper. S9 Ep12

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Manta/Berlinetta/TR7/BSA Bike: Dave travels to Bedale to extract a barn find - a 1984 Manta GTE which hasn't seen the light of day in thirty years. S9 Ep13

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: It's a Lovely Day Tomorrow: Laurence Olivier narrates the acclaimed documentary series on WWII. Hear how Japanese advances across Asia forced the Allies into ignominious retreat. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Home Fires: World War II as told by the late Laurence Olivier. Hear more about life on the British Home Front, a time of gas masks, digging for victory and evacuation. S1 Ep15

UAndYesterday.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Inside the Reich: Laurence Olivier narrates this 26-part series, a milestone in TV history. Germany's progress loses momentum as the tide of the war turns in favour of the Allies. S1 Ep16

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Armstrong Siddeley/Triumph Herald: Derek takes a shine to a rare 1958 Armstrong Siddeley Sapphire with a long family history and a convertible Triumph Herald brings a few smiles on auction day. S3 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: DB6/Merc Unimog Fire Engine: An Aston Martin DB6 in need of total restoration looks set to break the Mathewsons auction record and news of a rare Vincent motorbike arriving causes a stir. S3 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Jungles: Jungles provide the richest habitats on the planet - mysterious worlds of high drama where extraordinary animals attempt to survive in the most competitive places. S2 Ep3

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Deserts: The world's deserts force animals to come up with ingenious ways of coping with hostile conditions, giving rise to the most incredible survival stories on earth. S2 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Planet Earth
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Grasslands: Wildlife documentary series presented by David Attenborough. A look at survival in grasslands, from Asia's saiga antelope to the giant anteaters of Brazil. S2 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Waiting for God: Off-the-wall space comedy. Holly finds a pod which Rimmer believes to contain the body of a Quagaar warrior, a species with green hair and six breasts! S1 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Confidence and Paranoia: More escapades in space on board the Red Dwarf. Lister explores Kochanski's quarters and tries to find her hologram disc - with disastrous results. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Red Dwarf
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Me2: Space-set comedy. When two Rimmers appear, any thoughts that they might co-exist in harmony are soon put to rest and one of them must be switched off - but which one? S1 Ep6

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterday.uk.description: New. VW Beetle: Gus and Will want to buy a VW Beetle. They locate a guy selling a project car, but fear it's almost too good to be true at less than 1,000 pounds. S2 Ep8

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Swift/Toyota Corona/Bedford Van: Derek goes to pick up a veteran 1904 Swift, there's an emotional farewell to a 1980s Bedford HA van, and a Toyota Corona finds a new home. S9 Ep4

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: Alvis 12/50/Alfetta/RS2000: Derek gets a tour of Hadlow Castle in Kent when he arrives to collect the owner's pre-war Alvis and an immaculate Citroen used by the Gestapo in occupied France. S6 Ep7

UAndYesterday.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterday.uk.description: BMW Z4 Batmobile/Ford Army Jeep: Derek is picking up two expertly crafted Batmobile replicas in the home counties and Dave can't control his enthusiasm for a Ford US wartime jeep. S6 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: One Foot in the Grave
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Things Aren't Simple Anymore: The immensely moving final episode of the long-running sitcom, in which uber-grump Victor finally meets his maker. David Renwick leaves us with a twist. S6 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Alfa Romeo Giulia/Citroen 2CV6: Derek casts his eye over a Citroen 2CV, before he is off admiring the treasure trove of more than 270 motorbikes in the same garage. S6 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Zephyr/Autobianchi: Derek heads off to collect some vintage motorcycles from a garage at the bottom of the garden in the North-East of England. S6 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Capri/Alpine/Lancia Fulvia Zagato: Derek heads to Sunderland to pick up a real Italian beauty - a 1972 Lancia Fulvia Zagato. Red and racy, the car has seen better days but Derek's still impressed. S9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Austin Morris Minor: Up for sale at the Mathewson's auction is a 1275 Mini GT that's come from just down the road and could be a future British icon. S9 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Preserving Our Past: An insight into Fred Dibnah's love of restoring engines and chimneys, highlighting one of his greatest triumphs - his stream traction engine. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Teleshopping
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Forvie to Peterhead: Michael Portillo's Scottish railway journey reaches Aberdeen, from where he heads out to Forvie National Nature Reserve. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Inverness to the Cairngorms: Michael Portillo crosses the Culloden Viaduct aboard the Caledonian Sleeper to arrive bright and early in Inverness. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Cullen to Cawdor: Michael Portillo travels by train north from Inverness to the Orkney Islands. Beginning on the Moray Firth, Michael admires the Cullen Viaduct. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Coastal Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Invergordon to Tain: Michael Portillo's Scottish coastal railway journey reaches Invergordon on the Cromarty Firth, the third great inlet on the northeast coast of the Highlands. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Changing the Landscape: Fred Dibnah's interest in industrial engineering, which was sparked by the canals, railways and bridges built near his Bolton home. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Great British Builders: Fred Dibnah offers demonstrations of building techniques as he shares his appreciation for the skills of the great British builders. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Masters of Their Trade: An insight into Fred Dibnah's appreciation for the craftsmanship of the past and for the work of those people who still carry on the traditions. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: A Good Day's Work: The ex-steeplejack shares his enthusiasm for Britain's industrial heritage. In this final programme, Fred visits Warwick Castle and Ely Cathedral. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The First Railways: Fred Dibnah examines the work of the Stephenson family, and how it influenced the railways. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Changing the Landscape: Fred Dibnah explores how railways changed Britain and follows the growth in popularity of the locomotive. Plus, a visit to a rope haulage railway in Derbyshire. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Brunal and the Great Western: Fred Dibnah learns more about the work of one of his heroes, engineer Isambard Kingdom Brunel and his plans for a wide gauge railway system. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Great Days of Steam: Fred Dibnah explores the creation of the stream train and new speed records that were set in the 1920s. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Railway Preservation: Fred Dibnah explains how diesel-powered locomotives replaced steam trains, leading to the creation of the Railway Preservation Society. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Historic Railways: Fred Dibnah examines historic railways and engineering projects undertaken by the likes of Stephenson and Hackworth. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Narrow Gauge Railways: Fred Dibnah visits Ravenglass, Cumbria, where he has an opportunity to see an old mill working. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ffestiniog Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Ffestiniog Railway in Gwynedd, Wales, where he talks about restoration work and is taken for a ride down the track by the manager Paul. S1 Ep9

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Main Line Experience: Fred Dibnah visits Llangollen Railway, where he reminisces about the past, and is given a chance to fulfil a childhood dream with driver Robert Haslam. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bluebell Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Bluebell Railway in East Sussex. His first footplate ride of the day is on Fenchurch, where he is pleasantly surprised to meet a fire lady. S1 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Railway Yards and Workshops: Fred Dibnah explains what happens in railway works, visiting Bo'ness and Kinneil, Scotland, and the Boston Lodge in Ffestiniog, Wales. S1 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Midland Railway: Fred Dibnah visits the Midland Railway Centre in Derbyshire, is given a tour of the sheds and gets to have a go on the hydraulic riveter. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Railway Collection
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Severn Valley Railway: Fred Dibnah drives his own engine to Bridgnorth, Shropshire, to see an engine repair shed and purpose-built boiler shop. S1 Ep14

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Great Central Railway: Fred visits the Great Central Railway, the only remaining main line railway in the country which still has steam locomotives, where he takes a footplate ride. S1 Ep15
